July unemployment set a 40-year high in Connecticut, New Mexico, and New York.
All 50 states and DC saw a year-over-year increase in house prices from Q2 2019 to Q2 2020.
Hawaii and New York saw the largest declines in GDP from Q1 2019 to Q1 2020.
CT, NH, NY, and PA have all seen retail employment fall over 10% since July 2019.
State and local public employment is down 10% or more over the year in five states.
In July, average private-sector weekly earnings ranged from $774 in MS to $1,781 in DC.
Washington’s annual house price growth has exceeded the US average each quarter since 2014.
DC’s Q1 2020 GDP from accommodation and food services fell 9 percent compared to Q1 2019.
